    </p>

    <div class="skills-row">
      <span class="skills-label">Skills —</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">SolidWorks</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">OnShape</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">FEA</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">C++</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">Python</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">MATLAB</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">Composites Manufacturing</span>
      <span class="skill-chip">Instrumentation</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>

    <div class="filter-bar">
      <button class="filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="mechanical">Mechanical</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="software">Software</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="rocketry">Rocketry</button>
    </div>

    <div class="grid" id="grid">

      <!--
        HOW TO ADD A PROJECT:
        1. Copy a card block below
        2. Set data-category to match a filter button (e.g. "rocketry")
        3. Fill in the onclick values:
             - Title
             - Full description (2–4 sentences)
             - Media array: ['images/a.jpg', 'images/b.jpg', 'images/c.mp4']
             - Year
             - Tools used (comma-separated string)
             - Tags array (e.g. ['Rocketry', 'Design'])
        4. Update card-title, card-desc, card-year, tag spans
        5. Put files in an "images/" folder next to this HTML file
        NOTE: If a project has only 1 photo and no video, use a single-item array
              and remove the extra <img>/<video> lines and extra dots accordingly.
      -->

      <!-- PROJECT 1: Viper -->
      <div class="card"
           data-category="rocketry"
           onclick="openLightbox(
