             'My personal L1 Cert rocket, designed and built from scratch before finishing high school. After a recovery system failure caused major damage on its first flight, I repaired it and launched again in early 2025. It flew perfectly and deployed the parachutes correctly, earning me my L1 certification. This project taught me that failures are part of engineering, and that the real skill is learning from mistakes and making it work the next time.',
